Message.message: Press [R] to rewind to your last log entry.  If you really stuff up, start a new game.
I record a log of my experiences. It may be useful if I need to retrace my steps.
The station is devoid of air. The micro-meteors must have hit here too.
I'll have to find the other shuttle quickly.
These are typical zero-G crates that clamp to the floor when not being moved.
Let's see what useful stuff they're full of...
They're full of vacuum cleaners!
This looks promising!
They just don't make space stations like they used to.
Now I just need to release the docking clamps.
ERROR: Only one airlock may be powered at a time.
No, I'm not releasing the docking clamp on my shuttle.  That's my only life line right now.
